subSubSection.paragraph:
Male
. Body length 
11 mm
; fore wing length 
10.6 mm
. Structure as in female, but differing from latter as follows: head proportionally smaller, almost round, in frontal view as wide as high (
Fig. 8
). Vertex well developed, without cephalic fovea. Distance from posterior ocelli to apical margin of vertex about 2.6 × distance from posterior ocelli to inner eye margin (
Fig. 10
). Occipital carina complete, present along entire length of gena, but dorsally weaker. Inner eye margins in frontal view strongly convergent, about 1.5 × further apart from each other at vertex than at clypeus (
Fig. 8
). Clypeus in frontal view higher than wide, about 1.5 × as high as wide, apical margin deeply emarginated medially, forming blunt triangle tooth each lateral side (
Fig. 8
), width of emargination 1/2 × width of clypeus between inner eye margins; in lateral view disc of clypeus gradually and weekly convex from base to basal half, then going straightly to apical margin. Antennal scape about 5 × as long as its maximum width; flagellomere I about 1.7 × as long as its maximum width, flagellomeres II–IX longer than wide, flagellomere X small, as long as wide, terminal flagellomere slightly curved, slightly more than 2.5 × as long as its basal width (
Fig. 9
). Tergum III with well-developed apical lamella as in tergum II; tergum VII with short lamella and not raised.
